post_text:
It is critically important that parents and families do their part to slow the spread of COVID-19. This role for parents and families includes:
Limiting potential exposure to COVID-19 by social distancing, wearing masks, and avoiding large crowds.
Watching for potential symptoms and staying home when sick.
Getting tested when appropriate and staying home while waiting for test results.
While all are eager to return back to school and connect with others in our school community, staff, students, and families need to follow guidance about when they should NOT be in school. If you are sick, stay home and consider COVID-19 testing. If you have had close contact with a confirmed case of COVID-19 in your home or in other activities, stay out of school for the full 14 days of quarantine.
By staying home when you are sick or have been exposed to a positive case, you are helping your community stay in school together.

post_text:
Little Rams Childcare Registration!

Please register your children for the before & after school-aged childcare that Roseau School District offers! Due to COVID-19, we need to plan accordingly. We will only take children who are preregistered, so please fill out this quick Google Form! Childcare is for students in Kindergarten through 6th grade. The hours are from 6:00-8:00 AM & 3:15-5:30 PM. The cost is $1.75 per child and $1.50 per hour for each additional child in the same family. Please complete this Google Form for EACH child and register BEFORE school starts!
(In addition, there is also a paper registration that will be in the school mailing. If you prefer that method, please fill it out and send it to the elementary office.) If you have any questions, please contact Cheryl Hirst @ cheryl_hirst@roseauschool.org (463-6405).
https://forms.gle/vXPqRmvdw9WxcPuZA

I am so thankful for the support of our district residents. We are fortunate to live and work in a community that values education, our school and most importantly our students. Tonight‚Äôs election result is a victory for our students, our school district and our community. Thank you to all that have worked together on behalf of our students and the referendum. District residents, staff members, board members and administration (past and present) who all played a part in the process and helped us to get to where we are tonight as a district. Thank you for voting and thank you for your commitment to education and the Roseau School District. I could not be more proud of everyone involved in this process. To the parents, staff, alumni, grandparents, farmers and business owners who make up our district‚Ä¶.thank you for voting and thank you for your selfless commitment to the Roseau School District.

I could not be more proud to serve the Roseau School District.

Sincerely,

Tom Jerome, Superintendent

Roseau School District

post_text: Attention to all those interested in Driver's Education and Behind the Wheel Training. Due to the stay-at-home order extension issued by the Governor's office, we will continue to suspend behind the wheel training until further notice. Our start date for our Driver's Education classroom courses continues to be June 1st. Dependent on the continuation of the stay-at-home order into June we will either hold classes in person or virtually. As we receive more direction and information from the Governor's office we will inform students and their families of our means to deliver instruction. If you have any questions you can contact Kelsey Johnson, Community Education Director at 218-463-2770.

post_text: Join in on the fun with Community Ed.!
shared_text:
Roseau Community Education
March 27 at 9:02 PM ¬∑

Hey Everyone, Community Education has been trying to find ways to stay connected and reach out to you all; our wonderful partners, students, and community to let you know that we are here for you and want to continue to be a presence and support.

Starting Monday (March 30th) we will be sharing daily ideas/activities/support right here on our Facebook page. Under our posts, we would love for you to share a picture of you/your family taking part in that day's theme. If you complete and share an image of yourself participating in one of our weekly ideas you will automatically be entered into our live drawing on Friday -- WINNERS will receive a FREE spot in any Community Ed class of their choice when we resume (hopefully sooner than later!). Weekly posts will occur March 30th - May 1st with a new drawing each Friday.

We hope this will give you something to look forward to each day as well as things to keep you busy and entertained while you are at home! Stay safe and healthy!
